*Property-Based Testing: Live games and Standings*

The project uses Vitest(as a testing tool) and Fast-check to perform property based testing.

- Running the Property Based Tests:
1) Install Dependencies:
a)First install Vitest and fast-check by using the following command:
 npm install -D vitest fast-check


2) To run the tests:
Run the following command:
npx vitest --watch

or run the tests once: 
npx vitest


*Test Results* 
Output:
"Test Files  1 passed (1)
      Tests  4 passed (4)
   Start at  03:46:06
   Duration  831ms" 

The property based tests validate the game status implementation against a wide range of generated inputs to ensure the expected behavior and invariants are maintained across many possible scenarios. 

